"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:5.15\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">5.15</span> 标题：皮袋、酒袋、水袋（wineskin, water bag）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：אוֹב</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：’ov)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job32:19\">JOB 32:19</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：חֵמֶת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：chemeth)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:15\">GEN 21:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:19\">GEN 21:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:15\">HAB 2:15</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：נֹאד</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：no’d)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:4\">JOS 9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:13\">JOS 9:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:19\">JDG 4:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:20\">1SA 16:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:9\">PSA 56:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:83\">PSA 119:83</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：נֵבֶל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：nevel)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:24\">1SA 1:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:3\">1SA 10:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:18\">1SA 25:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:1\">2SA 16:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:37\">JOB 38:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:12\">JER 13:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:12\">JER 13:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:12\">JER 48:12</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：ἀσκοπυτίνη</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：askoputinē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt10:5\">JDT 10:5</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：ἀσκός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：askos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:17\">MAT 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:17\">MAT 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:17\">MAT 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:17\">MAT 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:22\">MRK 2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:22\">MRK 2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:22\">MRK 2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:22\">MRK 2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:37\">LUK 5:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:37\">LUK 5:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:37\">LUK 5:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:38\">LUK 5:38</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/OAI-0003_objects_tools.png\" alt=\"盛酒皮袋\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">盛酒皮袋 (Image generated by ChatGPT using OpenAI technology)</figcaption></figure>水袋或者酒袋通常用山羊皮或绵羊皮制成，也可以使用牛皮或者骆驼皮。取皮时，在颈部使皮与肉分离，接下来往后拉下整张皮，再进行鞣制，毛通常会刮掉，然后将内面翻到外面。皮袋有五个开口，就是四条腿和脖子的位置，其中的四个开口要缝合起来。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0488_waterskin.jpg\" alt=\"用兽皮盛装液体，通常是水或酒\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">用兽皮盛装液体，通常是水或酒 (Gary Todd, Israel Museum, CC0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>皮袋是用来装液体的，主要是葡萄酒或水。皮袋只能作短期储存，否则里面的液体会沾上皮革的味道。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>希伯来文<em>’ov</em> 只出现在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job32:19\">JOB 32:19</a> ，上下文清楚表明这个词的意思是“酒袋”。关于这节经文的讨论，参《〈约伯记〉手册》（<em>A Handbook on The Book of Job</em> ）第601—602页。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:9\">PSA 56:9</a> （《和》56:8）；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:15\">HAB 2:15</a> ：有些重要参考资料并没有看到这些经文也提到了酒袋。关于这些经文的讨论，参《〈诗篇〉手册》（<em>A Handbook on Psalms</em> ）第505—506页和《〈那鸿书〉、〈哈巴谷书〉和〈西番雅书〉手册》（<em>A Handbook on The Books of Nahum, Habakkuk, and Zephaniah</em> ）第105—106页。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:83\">PSA 119:83</a> ：这节经文的第一行可译为，“我如被丢弃的酒袋，毫无用处”（如<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> ）。在许多语言中，这种表达几乎毫无意义。因此，翻译者可以选择译作“我毫不重要”，或者是用当地的某种物品替代“酒袋”，例如发霉的袋子。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:17\">MAT 9:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:22\">MRK 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:37\">LUK 5:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:38\">LUK 5:38</a> ：新约中的这些平行经文指的是“酒袋”。许多翻译者试图用“瓶子”来替代“酒袋”，但这种译法并不理想，因为发酵的葡萄酒通常并不会胀碎玻璃瓶或瓦瓶，但却会使旧酒袋裂开。在不使用酒袋或者酒袋不为人知的地方，翻译者可能需要使用一些描述性的短语，例如，“皮制容器”、“扎紧的皮袋子”或“像瓶子的山羊皮”，并在脚注中给出比较详细的解释。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
